
üé® DAY 9 ‚Äì CSS | Introduction & Fundamentals

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üåê What is CSS?

**CSS (Cascading Style Sheets)** is used to **style and design web pages**.

* Controls colors, fonts, layout, spacing
* Works with HTML
* Makes websites **beautiful and responsive**

üìå HTML = structure
üìå CSS = style

---

üß† Why CSS is Important

* Separates content from design
* Improves user experience (UX)
* Makes websites responsive
* Reduces code duplication
* Used in all modern websites

---

üÜö HTML vs CSS

| HTML         | CSS         |
| ------------ | ----------- |
| Structure    | Styling     |
| Content      | Design      |
| What to show | How to show |

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üß± Ways to Apply CSS

1Ô∏è‚É£ Inline CSS

Written inside HTML tags.

```html
<h1 style="color: red;">Hello CSS</h1>
```

‚ùå Not recommended for large projects

---

2Ô∏è‚É£ Internal CSS

Written inside `<style>` tag.

```html
<style>
  h1 {
    color: blue;
  }
</style>
```

üìå Used for small pages

---

3Ô∏è‚É£ External CSS (Best Practice)

Written in a separate `.css` file.

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
```

‚úî Reusable
‚úî Clean code
‚úî Scalable

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üéØ CSS Syntax

```css
selector {
  property: value;
}
```

Example:

```css
p {
  color: green;
  font-size: 16px;
}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üéØ CSS Selectors

Basic Selectors

| Selector  | Example    |
| --------- | ---------- |
| Element   | `p {}`     |
| Class     | `.box {}`  |
| ID        | `#main {}` |
| Universal | `* {}`     |

---

üß© CSS Colors

CSS supports multiple color formats.

```css
color: red;
color: #ff0000;
color: rgb(255, 0, 0);
```

---

üî† CSS Fonts

```css
p {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  font-size: 18px;
  font-weight: bold;
}
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üìê CSS Box Model (Very Important)

Every HTML element is a box.

Box Model Parts

* Content
* Padding
* Border
* Margin

```css
div {
  padding: 10px;
  border: 2px solid black;
  margin: 15px;
}
```

---

üìè Width & Height

```css
div {
  width: 200px;
  height: 100px;
}
```

---

üîó CSS Units

| Unit  | Description        |
| ----- | ------------------ |
| px    | Fixed size         |
| %     | Relative           |
| em    | Relative to parent |
| rem   | Relative to root   |
| vw/vh | Viewport           |

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üì¶ CSS Display Property

```css
span {
  display: block;
}
```

Common Values

* `block`
* `inline`
* `inline-block`
* `none`

---

üß† CSS Comments

```css
/* This is a comment */
```

---

‚ùå Common Beginner Mistakes

* Using inline CSS everywhere
* Mixing CSS & HTML
* Ignoring box model
* Overusing ID selectors

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üí° Best Practices

* Use external CSS
* Use class selectors
* Keep CSS organized
* Use meaningful class names

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚úÖ DAY 9 ‚Äì Summary

* Learned what CSS is
* Ways to apply CSS
* CSS syntax & selectors
* Colors, fonts & units
* Box model fundamentals
